WEBVTT


00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.400
You're a few days out from a 2024 parliamentary election in Korea.

00:00:03.401 --> 00:00:06.401
There are 40 parties participating in this election.

00:00:06.402 --> 00:00:09.161
I've compiled a list of their election manifestos

00:00:09.162 --> 00:00:10.841
and translated them to English.

00:00:10.842 --> 00:00:13.341
Today we'll be discussing the Liberal parties

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:15.420
participating in the parliamentary election.

00:00:15.440 --> 00:00:18.800
First and largest Liberal party is the Democratic Party of Korea

00:00:18.801 --> 00:00:20.681
with their satellite party Together

00:00:20.682 --> 00:00:21.641
Democratic Alliance.

00:00:21.642 --> 00:00:25.881
Their election pledges include the introduction of a 4.5 day work week,

00:00:25.882 --> 00:00:26.921
realizing social structure

00:00:26.922 --> 00:00:28.921
that allows for the compatibility of marriage,

00:00:28.922 --> 00:00:32.001
birth and childcare, expanding the number of medical students,

00:00:32.002 --> 00:00:33.281
establishing an occupational

00:00:33.282 --> 00:00:35.641
safety and health system for all working people

00:00:35.642 --> 00:00:37.481
so that they do not die at work.

00:00:37.482 --> 00:00:38.321
Preventing crisis

00:00:38.322 --> 00:00:40.641
and creating an atmosphere of peace on the Korean Peninsula.

00:00:40.642 --> 00:00:43.661
The introduction of a universal basic income pilot plan,

00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:47.780
realizing of confident diplomacy with Japan based on historical fact,

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:49.880
complete reform of the prosecutor's office

00:00:49.881 --> 00:00:52.841
and the neutrality and democratic control of the police.

00:00:52.842 --> 00:00:53.361
And lastly,

00:00:53.362 --> 00:00:56.261
creating a civil service culture that meets the public's expectations.

00:00:56.560 --> 00:00:58.520
The next Liberal party participating in the election

00:00:58.521 --> 00:00:59.881
is the new Future Party.

00:00:59.882 --> 00:01:03.161
They want a complete decentralization of the presidential system

00:01:03.162 --> 00:01:06.241
and the introduction of a presidential runoff system when voting.

00:01:06.242 --> 00:01:08.401
They want to remove privileges of lawmakers,

00:01:08.402 --> 00:01:10.841
preventing members of parliament from legal prosecution.

00:01:10.842 --> 00:01:13.561
They want a lifetime ban on judges and prosecutors

00:01:13.562 --> 00:01:15.141
from serving in the National Assembly.

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:17.960
They want to enact the basic acts for the working people

00:01:17.961 --> 00:01:21.041
to protect those currently exempt from the Labor Standard Act.

00:01:21.042 --> 00:01:23.561
They want a 35 hour work week without a cut to pay

00:01:23.562 --> 00:01:26.881
and expand annual leave from 15 days to 25 days.

00:01:26.882 --> 00:01:29.861
They want to completely nationalize local fire departments.

00:01:30.040 --> 00:01:32.120
They want to establish an office of immigration

00:01:32.121 --> 00:01:33.481
under the Public Administration

00:01:33.482 --> 00:01:36.361
and security and grand amnesty for migrant children.

00:01:36.362 --> 00:01:38.561
They want to abolish the military conscription system

00:01:38.562 --> 00:01:42.361
and move towards a completely volunteer military service program.

00:01:42.362 --> 00:01:45.641
And they also want to relocate the national capital to Sejong City.

00:01:45.642 --> 00:01:49.141
The next Liberal party participating is Rebuilding Korea Party.

00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.400
They want a complete decentralization of powerful

00:01:51.401 --> 00:01:53.161
prosecutorial authorities

00:01:53.162 --> 00:01:56.041
through the complete separation of investigation and prosecution.

00:01:56.042 --> 00:02:00.321
They want a direct election of prosecutors and indictment jury systems.

00:02:00.322 --> 00:02:03.241
Currently South Korea's on its 6th constitution

00:02:03.242 --> 00:02:04.641
and the Rebuilding Korea Party

00:02:04.642 --> 00:02:07.281
wants to create a seventh Republic of Korea

00:02:07.282 --> 00:02:09.401
by adopting a new constitution.

00:02:09.402 --> 00:02:13.281
They want to increase the portion of renewable energies to 30% by 2030

00:02:13.282 --> 00:02:16.801
and 80% by 2050. They want to reduce the burden of employment, housing,

00:02:16.802 --> 00:02:19.441
childcare and support for young women and young people

00:02:19.442 --> 00:02:22.181
by establishing a child rearing friendly society.

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:25.600
They want to inspire individuals will for potential growth,

00:02:25.601 --> 00:02:27.741
enhancing vitality of society as a whole

00:02:27.760 --> 00:02:29.540
through educational innovation.

00:02:29.560 --> 00:02:32.100
They want to strengthen local economic competitiveness

00:02:32.240 --> 00:02:35.560
through national financial decentralization.

00:02:35.561 --> 00:02:38.641
They want to implement foreign security policies

00:02:38.642 --> 00:02:40.961
that prevent war on the Korean Peninsula

00:02:40.962 --> 00:02:43.241
and lead to peace and prosperity in East Asia.

00:02:43.242 --> 00:02:43.801
And lastly,

00:02:43.802 --> 00:02:47.401
they seek to transform interkorean relations to peaceful coexistence

00:02:47.402 --> 00:02:49.361
based on Cooperation and solidarity.

00:02:49.362 --> 00:02:51.761
Last Liberal party is the New Progressive Union.

00:02:51.762 --> 00:02:53.641
They have one candidate in Daegu.

00:02:53.642 --> 00:02:57.021
Their national candidates are participating on the Democratic Party

00:02:57.040 --> 00:02:58.640
proportional representation list.

00:02:58.641 --> 00:03:02.301
They want 60% share of renewable energies by 2035.

00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:05.220
They want vouchers for electric vehicles and solar panels.

00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:07.640
They wanna see a basic income of half a million Korean

00:03:07.641 --> 00:03:10.441
one per month for two years to young people aged 20.

00:03:10.442 --> 00:03:12.121
They want a basic income of 300,000,

00:03:12.122 --> 00:03:15.741
one for farmers. They wanna see free tickets for public transportation.

00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:19.240
They want a four day 32 hour work week with no reduction in pay.

00:03:19.241 --> 00:03:21.921
They want to enact an anti discrimination law that covers gender,

00:03:21.922 --> 00:03:23.401
sexual orientation, disability,

00:03:23.402 --> 00:03:24.921
race and employment status.

00:03:24.922 --> 00:03:26.681
They want to abolish the death penalty.

00:03:26.682 --> 00:03:30.241
And lastly, they want to establish a National Students Human Rights Act

00:03:30.242 --> 00:03:33.281
and guarantee the participation of children and adolescents in school

00:03:33.282 --> 00:03:34.181
steering committees.

00:03:34.200 --> 00:03:36.828
Join us next time as we discuss the conservative camp.
